<HTMLSelectElementRequired>
<summary>
The <strong><c>required</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLSelectElement"/> interface specifies that the user must select an option with a non-empty string value before submitting a form. It reflects the {{htmlelement("select")}} element's <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/select#required"><c>required</c></see> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/select">select</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLSelectElement.Validity"/><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:required">:required</see> pseudo-class<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLSelectElement/required"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A boolean.</value>
</HTMLSelectElementRequired>
